    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nSometimes I'll bork my neovim config in a very verbose way. Neovim will generate lots of errors that I have to press `enter` repeatedly to go through. This makes it really difficult to repair my config because I lose all my plugins while I'm editing my neovim configuration.\n\nIt would be really great if there was some setting that could suppress those errors from popping up.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nA way to suppress the errors (write them to a file instead perhaps?) so I can use the existing config to repair the configuration.",
