            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I mean that using neovim when there are errors essentially on every keystroke make it unusable (even if the errors don't abort script execution. Most of the time they don't in my experience. E.g. all plugins load but one or a couple). \n\nFor example, I could be needing to include five `Enter` keystrokes between each input keystroke due to some really verbose errors. This renders Neovim very difficult to use. When I say \"lose all my plugins\" I mean not that the plugins aborted but that to circumvent all these very verbose errors, I will run neovim without any configuration to get a usable editor to fix my config with.\n\nIf these errors could be suppressed, then I could carry on fixing my config with the plugins that managed to be loaded.",
